---
layout: base
permalink: /index.html
title: 'Fudge Factor 🤔💡🤯🤓'
description: 'Fudge Factor 🤔💡🤯🤓 is the newsletter and blog of Jay Cuthrell'
blog:
  title: 'Recent Posts'
  intro: "Enjoy..."
---

<div class="wrapper">
  <header class="full | section" style="--spot-color: var(--color-primary)">
    <div class="section__inner flow region">
      <h1 class="text-center" style="color: var(--color-light);">{{ title }}</h1>
    </div>
    {% svg "divider/edgy", null, "divider" %}
  </header>

<div class="region flow">
  <div id="search" class="search-ui"></div>
</div>

<link href="/pagefind/pagefind-ui.css" rel="stylesheet">
<script src="/pagefind/pagefind-ui.js"></script>

<script>
  window.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', (event) => {
    new PagefindUI({ 
      element: "#search", 
      showSubResults: true,
      showImages: false 
    });
  });
</script>

<style>
  /* Optional: Tweak these variables to match your site's colors */
  .search-ui {
    --pagefind-ui-scale: 1;
    --pagefind-ui-primary: var(--color-primary, #333);
    --pagefind-ui-text: var(--color-text, #333);
    --pagefind-ui-background: var(--color-bg, #fff);
    --pagefind-ui-border: var(--color-border, #ccc);
    --pagefind-ui-font: var(--font-base, sans-serif); 
  }
</style>

  <section class="full | region">
    <div class="wrapper flow prose">
      <div class="feature |  region region-space-l">
        
        {% set itemList = collections.allPosts %}
        
        <!-- AEO/SEO: ItemList Schema -->
        <script type="application/ld+json">
        {
          "@context": "https://schema.org",
          "@type": "ItemList",
          "itemListElement": [
            {% set schemaList = collections.allPosts %}
            {% for item in schemaList.slice(0, 10) %}
            {
              "@type": "ListItem",
              "position": {{ loop.index }},
              "url": "{{ item.url | absoluteUrl(meta.url) }}"
            }{% if not loop.last %},{% endif %}
            {% endfor %}
          ]
        }
        </script>

        <!-- Visual Grid Layout -->
        <custom-masonry layout="50-50">
          {% asyncEach item in itemList.slice(0, 10) %}
            {% set headingLevel = "h3" %}
            {% include "partials/card-blog.njk" %}
          {% endeach %}
        </custom-masonry>
          <hr>
          <a href="{{ meta.url }}">{{meta.siteName}}</a> has been many things over the years as an archive of writing from <a href="{{ meta.author.website }}">{{ meta.author.name }}</a> since the late 1990s. The latest version of <a href="{{ meta.url }}">{{meta.siteName}}</a> is based on an amazing starter called <a href="https://github.com/madrilene/eleventy-excellent">Eleventy Excellent</a> by <a href="https://www.lenesaile.com/en/">Lene Saile</a>.  
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>